cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a video object segmentation algorithm based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and focuses on computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a feature compression technique, which involves reducing the memory requirements while maintaining the capability of feature representation, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions pre-training and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in deep learning, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with video data, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the transferability of the network to different domains, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
